Use this command to train:

parlai train_model -t fromfile:parlaiformat --fromfile-datapath data/SOMEFILE -m transformer/generator --init-model zoo:tutorial_transformer_generator/model --dict-file zoo:tutorial_transformer_generator/model.dict --embedding-size 512 --n-layers 8 --ffn-size 2048 --dropout 0.1 --n-heads 16 --learn-positional-embeddings True --n-positions 512 --variant xlm --activation gelu --fp16 True --text-truncate 512 --label-truncate 128 --dict-tokenizer bpe --dict-lower True -lr 1e-06 --optimizer adamax --lr-scheduler reduceonplateau --gradient-clip 0.1 -veps 0.25 --betas 0.9,0.999 --update-freq 1 --attention-dropout 0.0 --relu-dropout 0.0 --skip-generation True -vp 15 -stim 60 -vme 20000 -bs 16 -vmt ppl -vmm min --save-after-valid True --model-file model-runs/SOMEDIR/model --metrics ppl,bleu-4,rouge-L --tensorboard-log True

obviously replace SOMEDIR and SOMEFILE

Other options:
--dynamic-batching full
--fromfile-datatype-extension true
--num-epochs 1000


Model predictions on dataset
parlai display_model --task fromfile:parlaiformat --fromfile-datapath data/SOMEFILE -mf model-runs/SOMEDIR/model --num-examples 20



